# Azure Deployment Plan - Medicine Management System

## Architecture
- Frontend: React/Vite static site on Azure Static Web Apps
- Backend: Node.js/Express API on Azure App Service (Linux)
- Data/Auth: Existing Firebase project (Firestore + Auth)

## Required Environment Variables

### Backend App Service settings
- PORT=8080
- FRONTEND_URL=https://<your-static-web-app-domain>
- FIREBASE_WEB_API_KEY=<firebase-web-api-key>
- FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=<firebase-project-id>
- FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=<firebase-admin-client-email>
- FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=<firebase-admin-private-key-with-escaped-newlines>

### Frontend Static Web App settings
- VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://<your-backend-app-name>.azurewebsites.net/api
- VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=<firebase-api-key>
- VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=<firebase-project>.firebaseapp.com
- VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=<firebase-project-id>
- VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=<firebase-project>.firebasestorage.app
- VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=<messaging-sender-id>
- VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=<firebase-app-id>

## One-Time Prerequisites
- Install Azure CLI
- Create resource group and choose region
- Ensure Node 20 runtime is used for backend

## Deployment Steps

### 1) Backend - Azure App Service
1. In terminal, run:

```bash
az login
az group create --name rg-medicine-app --location centralindia
az appservice plan create --name asp-medicine-api --resource-group rg-medicine-app --sku B1 --is-linux
az webapp create --resource-group rg-medicine-app --plan asp-medicine-api --name <unique-backend-app-name> --runtime "NODE:20-lts"
```

2. Configure backend env vars:

```bash
az webapp config appsettings set --resource-group rg-medicine-app --name <unique-backend-app-name> --settings \
PORT=8080 \
FRONTEND_URL=https://<your-static-web-app-domain> \
FIREBASE_WEB_API_KEY="<firebase-web-api-key>" \
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID="<firebase-project-id>" \
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL="<firebase-admin-client-email>" \
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="<private-key-with-escaped-newlines>"
```

3. Deploy backend code:

```bash
cd backend
npm ci
zip -r backend.zip . -x "node_modules/*"
az webapp deploy --resource-group rg-medicine-app --name <unique-backend-app-name> --src-path backend.zip --type zip
```

4. Validate health:

```bash
curl https://<unique-backend-app-name>.azurewebsites.net/health
```

### 2) Frontend - Azure Static Web Apps
1. Push this repo to GitHub (if not already).
2. In Azure Portal, create Static Web App and connect GitHub repo.
3. Use build config:
- App location: frontend
- Output location: dist
- API location: (leave blank)

4. Add frontend environment variables in Static Web App configuration (Production slot).
5. Trigger redeploy from GitHub Actions after setting variables.

## Post-Deploy Tasks
- Update backend FRONTEND_URL to the final static web app URL.
- Update frontend VITE_API_BASE_URL to the backend URL.
- Deploy Firestore rules/indexes if needed:

```bash
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules --project <your-project-id>
firebase deploy --only firestore:indexes --project <your-project-id>
```

## Security Follow-up (Important)
- Rotate Firebase Admin private key because sensitive credentials were previously present in example files.
- Keep backend/serviceAccountKey.json out of git.
